---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CTAButton from '../components/CTAButton.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Real Resource Economics"
  description="Real Resource Economics — the work of Stephen Laughton, author of The Money Sham (Lola Books)."
>
  <h1>Real Resource Economics</h1>

  <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-[color:var(--color-charcoal)]">
    Real Resource Economics asks a simple question: what can our economy
    actually do, given the people, materials, and energy available to it? It
    starts from real capacity rather than from money, and treats public spending
    decisions as choices about what to build, who to employ, and what to leave
    undone — not as questions of affordability. <em>[Placeholder lede — Steve to
    revise.]</em>
  </p>

  <p class="mt-4">
    Stephen Laughton is a writer and former financial professional. His book
    <em>The Money Sham</em> sets out the case for Real Resource Economics in
    plain language. <em>[Placeholder bio.]</em>
  </p>

  <div class="mt-10 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
    <CTAButton
      href="https://www.lolabooks.eu/products/the-money-sham-stephen-laughton"
      external
    >
      Read the Book
    </CTAButton>
    <CTAButton href="/policies" variant="outline">
      Explore the Ideas
    </CTAButton>
  </div>

  <hr class="my-12 border-[color:var(--color-rule)]" />

  <section>
    <h2 class="!mt-0">Related work: MMTUK</h2>
    <p>
      Many of the ideas in <em>The Money Sham</em> sit alongside the work of
      MMTUK, the UK's first MMT-driven policy research organisation. See
      <a href="https://mmtuk.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">mmtuk.org</a>
      for related policy papers and briefings.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
